{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
These [D]rough old hands are glued to the wheel
Five foot of fence from the way that they feel
And the [A]lights coming over the hill are a [D]blinding me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_chorus}
There’s [A]rain on the road and I can see the load start to shiftin’
