And I [A]can’t believe this is really happening [D]to me
{end_of_chorus}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
God I’m [D]over the edge and down the mountain side
I [G]know they’ll tell about the night I died
Between [A]the rain and the lights on the hill  are a [D]blindin’ me
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
It’s a [D]long tough road from a way down south
A [G]mans gotta find a little food for his mouth
And a [A]home for a girl as sweet as honey [D]can be
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
So it’s [D]down through the gears shes a startin to pull
The [G]gage on the tank is a showin’ full
